maml:description.maml:para: Deletes temporary Azure files used by signing service

As part of the signing process, the user is given temporary access to an Azure Blob container to upload their file to be signed. Once the service completes signing, the user can download the file from the Azure Blob container. The temporary access is set to expire after a given time (by default 12 hours). This script goes through all the temporary Azure containers used by the singing service (containers with names starting with the word "deletable") and deletes those where the user's temporary access has expired.
